This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for facial attribute detection, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of deep convolutional neural networks also suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses modifications to existing datasets, which could place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The use of committee machine techniques for combining local and global decisions suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential security implications of facial attribute detection, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
